# Filter Tree — Grouped Expressions with Bracket Support
#
# Replaces the flat Map<string, Filter> model with a recursive tree
# supporting nested AND/OR groups, drag-to-group, inline editing,
# and visual bracket rendering in the FilterBar.
#
# Current state: flat Map<string, Filter> + global AND/OR toggle
# Target state:  FilterNode tree with nested groups + per-group AND/OR
#
# Blast radius: ~23 files, all within data-table-v3 (no app package changes)
# The package's external API (initialFilters prop, onFilterChange callback)
# uses serialized format, so tree changes are contained.
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PHASE 1: DATA MODEL & ENGINE (Foundation — must be done first)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# This phase changes the core data representation. Everything else
# depends on it. Aim to keep the existing flat UI working during
# this phase by providing a compatibility shim that flattens the
# tree for components not yet updated.

## Phase 1A: Type definitions
  File: src/lib/types/filters.ts

  - [ ] Define FilterLeaf type (wraps a single Filter + unique nodeId)
        ```
        interface FilterLeaf {
          nodeType: 'leaf';
          nodeId: string;          // crypto.randomUUID() or nanoid
          filter: Filter;          // existing Filter union (text/numeric/date/set/boolean)
        }
        ```

  - [ ] Define FilterGroup type (recursive container)
        ```
        interface FilterGroup {
          nodeType: 'group';
          nodeId: string;
          combination: FilterCombination;  // 'AND' | 'OR'
          children: FilterNode[];
        }
        ```

  - [ ] Define FilterNode union: FilterLeaf | FilterGroup

  - [ ] Define FilterTree type (root is always a FilterGroup)
        ```
        interface FilterTree {
          root: FilterGroup;
        }
        ```

  - [ ] Add helper type: FlatFilterEntry = { nodeId: string; filter: Filter; path: string[] }
        (path = array of parent group nodeIds, for breadcrumb/nesting depth)

  - [ ] Export all new types from types/filters.ts

  - [ ] Decision: keep FilterCombination as 'AND' | 'OR' (no XOR/NAND — not needed for clinical data)

## Phase 1B: Tree utility functions
  New file: src/lib/utils/filterTree.ts

  - [ ] createFilterTree(): FilterTree — empty root AND group
  - [ ] createLeaf(filter): FilterLeaf — wraps filter with generated nodeId
  - [ ] createGroup(combination, children?): FilterGroup
  - [ ] addFilter(tree, filter, parentGroupId?): FilterTree — adds leaf to group (default: root)
  - [ ] removeNode(tree, nodeId): FilterTree — removes leaf or group by nodeId
  - [ ] updateFilter(tree, nodeId, filter): FilterTree — updates leaf's filter
  - [ ] moveNode(tree, nodeId, targetGroupId, insertIndex): FilterTree — moves node between groups
  - [ ] groupNodes(tree, nodeIds, combination): FilterTree — wraps selected nodes in a new group
  - [ ] ungroupNode(tree, groupId): FilterTree — dissolves group, moves children to parent
  - [ ] findNode(tree, nodeId): FilterNode | null
  - [ ] findParentGroup(tree, nodeId): FilterGroup | null
  - [ ] getLeafFilters(tree): Filter[] — flattens tree to array (compatibility shim)
  - [ ] getLeafCount(tree): number — count of leaf filters
  - [ ] getFilterByColumnId(tree, columnId): FilterLeaf | null — find first filter for column
  - [ ] setFilterForColumn(tree, columnId, filter | null): FilterTree — add/update/remove by columnId
        (backwards-compatible with current handleFilterChange signature)
  - [ ] mapLeaves(tree, fn): FilterTree — transform every leaf filter
  - [ ] filterTreeToMap(tree): Map<string, Filter> — compatibility: extract columnId→Filter map

  All functions return new objects (immutable updates, no mutation).

  Tests: src/lib/utils/__tests__/filterTree.test.ts
  - [ ] Write tests for every function above
  - [ ] Test deeply nested trees (3+ levels)
  - [ ] Test edge cases: empty tree, single leaf, remove last child dissolves group

## Phase 1C: Recursive filter engine
  File: src/lib/engines/filterData.ts

  - [ ] Add overload: filterData(data, tree: FilterTree, options?)
        Keep existing filterData(data, filters: Filter[], options?) for backwards compatibility
  - [ ] Implement evaluateNode(row, node): boolean
        - If leaf: apply single filter (reuse existing applySingleFilter)
        - If group: evaluate children with group's combination (AND = every, OR = some)
  - [ ] Short-circuit evaluation: AND stops on first false, OR stops on first true
  - [ ] Handle enabled flag on leaves (skip disabled leaves)
  - [ ] Handle empty groups (AND with no children = true, OR with no children = false)

  Tests: src/lib/engines/__tests__/filterTree.test.ts
  - [ ] Flat tree (root AND with 3 leaves) matches existing behavior
  - [ ] Nested: (A AND B) OR C
  - [ ] Nested: A AND (B OR C)
  - [ ] Deep: ((A AND B) OR (C AND D)) AND E
  - [ ] Mixed types: text + numeric + set in same group
  - [ ] Disabled leaves skipped
  - [ ] Empty groups handled correctly

## Phase 1D: Serialization
  File: src/lib/utils/filterSerialization.ts

  - [ ] Add serializeFilterTree(tree: FilterTree): SerializedFilterTree
  - [ ] Add deserializeFilterTree(data: SerializedFilterTree): FilterTree
  - [ ] Define SerializedFilterTree / SerializedFilterNode types
        (same structure but Dates → ISO strings, no functions)
  - [ ] Backward compatibility: if deserialize receives a flat SerializedFilter[],
        auto-wrap in a root AND group (migration path for existing localStorage data)

  File: src/lib/utils/PerDatasetPersistence.ts
  - [ ] Update DatasetViewState.activeFilters type to SerializedFilterTree
  - [ ] Add migration logic: detect old Map format → convert to tree on load
  - [ ] Update saveFilters() to serialize tree
  - [ ] Update loadState() to deserialize tree

  Tests: src/lib/utils/__tests__/filterSerialization.test.ts
  - [ ] Round-trip: serialize → deserialize preserves tree structure
  - [ ] Backward compat: flat array → tree migration
  - [ ] Date handling in nested leaves

## Phase 1E: State management migration
  File: src/lib/state/tableState.svelte.ts

  - [ ] Replace `let filters = $state<Map<string, Filter>>(new Map())`
        with `let filterTree = $state<FilterTree>(createFilterTree())`
  - [ ] Replace `let filtersByDataset` to store FilterTree per dataset
  - [ ] Update processData() to call filterData(rawData, filterTree)
  - [ ] Keep handleFilterChange(columnId, filter | null) signature working
        via setFilterForColumn() shim — this is the compat bridge
  - [ ] Add new tree-aware handlers:
        - handleAddFilterToGroup(filter, groupId?)
        - handleRemoveNode(nodeId)
        - handleUpdateFilter(nodeId, filter)
        - handleMoveNode(nodeId, targetGroupId, index)
        - handleGroupNodes(nodeIds, combination)
        - handleUngroupNode(groupId)
        - handleGroupCombinationChange(groupId, combination)
  - [ ] Expose in return object:
        - get filterTree()
        - get filters() — compatibility getter via filterTreeToMap()
        - All new handlers above
  - [ ] Update serialization in dataset init (deserialize tree, handle migration)
  - [ ] Update onFilterChange callback to emit serialized tree
        Decision: emit SerializedFilterTree (breaking) or keep SerializedFilter[] (compat)?
        Recommendation: emit both — onFilterChange gets flat array, onFilterTreeChange gets tree

## Phase 1F: Component compatibility shim
  Ensure existing components keep working with minimal changes before Phase 2.

  File: src/lib/ClinicalDataTableV3.svelte
  - [ ] Pass state.filters (compat Map) to FilterRow, ChartFilterRow, StatusBar
  - [ ] Pass state.filterTree to FilterBar (will be updated in Phase 2)
  - [ ] Update filterCount to use getLeafCount(state.filterTree)
  - [ ] Add new prop: onFilterTreeChange?: (tree: SerializedFilterTree) => void
  - [ ] Keep initialFilters prop working (backward compat via migration)
  - [ ] Add optional initialFilterTree prop

  File: src/lib/TableHeader/FilterRow.svelte — no changes yet (uses compat Map)
  File: src/lib/components/chart-filters/ChartFilterRow.svelte — no changes yet
  File: src/lib/components/chart-filters/ColumnChart.svelte — no changes yet
  File: src/lib/components/chart-filters/CategoricalChart.svelte — no changes yet
  File: src/lib/TableFooter/StatusBar.svelte — no changes yet

  At end of Phase 1: all existing tests pass, UI looks the same, tree is internal.

